      <hedline>
        <hl1>Soprano's Piano</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>June Oliansky letter on August 20 travel article notes she was given permission to play a few notes on opera singer Marcella Sembrich's piano at studio in Bolton Landing, NY; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: My husband and I have been opera fans for many years, and we visited Marcella Sembrich's studio at Bolton Landing, N.Y., last summer (''A Voice From the Met's Final Season,'' Aug. 20). The curator, Richard Wargo, was most informative, and when I asked him if I could play a few notes on Miss Sembrich's Steinway, he kindly gave me permission. Imagine my thrill as I sat at the very piano on which she played and gave lessons.</p>
        <p>JUNE OLIANSKY  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
